From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-20)
Subject: [PATCH] tasks/task-flow: add octo_mirrored sync mode and octo.mission step vocabulary

Extend Task Flow with the minimal upstream surface needed to host
mirrored Octopus Orchestrator missions as first-class flow records,
per OCTO-DEC-030 (mirrored-mode default) and OCTO-DEC-033 (bridge
file placement).

Adds:
  - TaskFlowSyncMode variant "octo_mirrored" — an observer-only
    projection sibling to the existing "task_mirrored" mode. State
    of record lives in the Octopus event log; Task Flow reflects it.
  - OCTO_MISSION_STEP_TYPE = "octo.mission" — reserved currentStep
    vocabulary entry for octo-mirrored flows. Task Flow's currentStep
    is free-form today, so this is a vocabulary reservation.
  - createTaskFlowForOctoMission — named constructor, thin wrapper
    over createFlowRecord with observer-mode defaults.
  - applyOctoMissionEvent — narrow event ingestion seam that maps
    a fixed set of octo event kinds to FlowRecordPatch updates via
    the existing updateFlowRecordByIdExpectedRevision path.

No behavior change for deployments with octo.enabled: false (default
through Milestone 1): the new sync mode is unreachable, the new
exports are unused, and every existing task-flow-registry caller is
untouched.

Downstream octo consumer binds to this surface via
src/octo/adapters/openclaw/taskflow-bridge.ts (placeholder from
Octopus M0-10). No other Octopus code imports Task Flow directly.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

